Section2.Para:
We evaluated the following six methods:

                      1.


Spatio-Temporal DCDs (abbreviated as ’STDCD’);



                      2.


MFCCs-based signature (’MFC’);



                      3.


Combination of methods (1) and (2) (’STDCD+MFC’);



                      4.


Hua et al. method [9] (’HUA’);



                      5.


Itoh et al. method [13] (’IT’);



                      6.


Anguera et al. method [14] (’ANG’).


                  Our methods [methods (1), (2), and (3)] include different combinations of the proposed techniques. More precisely, in method (1), visual fingerprints based on Spatio-temporal DCDs are extracted as described in Sect. 3 and are utilized for the copy detection task. MFCCs-based audio signatures are generated as illustrated in Sect. 4 and are employed for the CBCD task in method (2). In method (3), spatio-temporal dominant color features and MFCCs-based audio fingerprints are jointly utilized by employing fusion strategies to identify the duplicate video sequences.
